The paper presents a new classification approach for hyperspectral data analysis using tensor algebra. This involves both linear and nonlinear models, which are trained using learning algorithms. Given that the paper focuses on image analysis and machine learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
